                                         CAPE TOWN – At least 270 people have been left homeless after a fire broke out in Chicago, Paarl East, in the Western Cape. The blaze started in the early hours of Sunday morning. The Drakenstein fire department says 14 housing units located in four blocks of flats, as well as 42 informal structures, have been destroyed. Three housing units in Grysbok flats have also been damaged. Drakenstein acting mayor Riaan Smuts says: “There is one lady in hospital but we will get confirmation from Paarl Hospital later.”